#: en/mbrpra-sessions.tex:88
msgid "\n		\\item Self-compassion is about being kind, gentle, and understanding towards ourselves. Self-compassion helps us work through from setbacks and slips in the recovery process.\n		\\item Self-compassion means not judging ourselves when we are upset or having a hard time. We can pause and tell ourselves \\toSelf{It’s okay to feel upset. I am doing the best I can.}\n		\\item All human beings struggle. No one is perfect. When we practice self-compassion, we can tell ourselves: \\toSelf{I’m not alone feeling this way. We all go through hard times.}\n	"
msgstr ""

