#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:13
msgid "About Mindfulness-Based Relapse Prevention"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:14
msgid "Mindfulness-Based Relapse Prevention (MBRP) is a program designed to prevent relapse, in prevention of or recovery from addiction — in the wide sense (repeated behavior leading to significant harm and distress), including:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:17
msgid "\n		\\item substance addictions (alcohol, drugs, tobacco, medicaments);\n		\\item addictive behaviors:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:20
msgid "\n				\\item external: food, work, sport, sex, pornography, gambling, self-harm, shopping, …;\n				\\item internal: frequent self-criticism or devaluation of others, aggressiveness, anxiety, submissiveness, …\n			"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:25
msgid "\\textbf{Mindfulness} is being aware of our present moment experience (such as how we feel or what is going on around us) in an open and nonjudgmental way."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:28
msgid "MBRP is a structured training of the skill of mindfulness using various guided exercises. The ability to stay oriented in one’s experience as it unfolds reduces the likelihood of relapse — falling back into the addictive behavior."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:29
msgid "MBRP can help you:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:35
msgid "\n		\\item Be more aware of relapse triggers.\n		\\item Respond/cope with triggers (not just react).\n		\\item Work with difficult emotions in healthy ways.\n		\\item Be kinder and more compassionate towards yourself.\n		\\item Develop a lifestyle that promotes long-term recovery.\n	"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:38
msgid "Research of mindfulness and MBRP"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:39
msgid "Research shows that learning and practicing mindfulness…"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:41
msgid "Reduces the odds of relapsing to alcohol or drug use."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:42
msgid "Reduces urges/cravings to use alcohol or drugs."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:43
msgid "Improves emotional well-being."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:46
msgid "Research results are described in articles referenced at XXX."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:47
msgid "Structure"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:48
msgid "The MBRP programme has three pillars, main components. They are all recommended, but also voluntary."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:49
msgid "Formal mindfulness practices:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:50
msgid "Informal practices:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:50
msgid "regular (e.g. daily) practice with guided meditation recordings, in dedicated time."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:51
msgid "Support group meetings:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:51
msgid "bringing mindfulness into activities and situations throughout your daily life."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:52
msgid "sharing the experience, support from the group, regularity and structure for the practice. Groups are facilitated by a trained professional."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:62
msgid "Formal Practices"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:63
msgid "There are 12 guided meditations altogether, listed below. Each session recommends practices for the next week."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:66
msgid "\n		\\item All recorded meditations are available at \\href{https://PracticeMBRP.com}{PracticeMBRP.com}, you can play them on a computer or phone.\n		\\item You can also download and use the recordings in other suitable ways (offline from the phone, MP3 player, mindfulness app)\n	"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:68
msgid "It is beneficial to establish regularity of the practice, a routine. Example practice routines:"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:69
msgid "John"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:70
msgid "Emily"
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:70
msgid "I listen to a 5- or 10-minute audio-guided mindfulness exercise about 6 days a week. I practice before breakfast in the morning. I sit in a chair. Practicing at the same time every day helps me remember to practice. I go to the website PracticeMBRP.com on my smartphone and play the recordings from there. I make mindfulness practice a part of my life because it helps me be more aware of what is going on and helps me stay on track with my recovery."
msgstr ""

#: en/mbrpra-start.tex:71
msgid "I listen to a 10 or 15-minute audio-guided mindfulness exercise about 5 days a week. I practice at night after I shower and put on my pajamas. I sit in my bed and use pillows to support my back. I play the recordings from a MP3 player I borrowed from my therapist. I also use headphones to block out other noise. When I stick to a regular practice routine, I feel more grounded and I am better able to deal with stress that comes up in my life."
msgstr ""

